oliday chalets and student hostels will be prepared as government quarantine centres.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Toh |first1=Ting Wei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/quarantine-places-including-chalets-being-prepared-as-singapore-fights-spread-of |title=Wuhan virus: Quarantine centres, including chalets, being prepared as Singapore fights spread of disease |date=24 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref> In addition, several companies have since taken more precautions against the virus.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Iau |first1=Jean |last2=Wong |first2=Lester |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-comfortdelgro-stockpiles-masks-and-disinfectants-issues-health-and-travel |title=Wuhan virus: ComfortDelGro, SMRT, private-hire car operators step up preventive measures |date=24 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> A Scoot flight was delayed for six hours after one passenger was sent for further tests,<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Baharudin |first1=Hariz |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/wuhan-virus-man-on-scoot-flight-from-singapore-to-china-sent-for-further-tests-all |title=Wuhan virus: Scoot making arrangements to bring back Singaporean passengers, crew quarantined in Hangzhou |date=25 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref> with the flight returning to Singapore three days later.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Kua |first1=Yu-Lin |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-18-singapore-residents-and-10-scoot-staff-back-home-from-hangzhou-on-a-scoot |title=Wuhan virus: 18 Singapore residents and 10 Scoot staff back home from Hangzhou on a Scoot relief flight |date=27 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n**25 January - No new cases are confirmed with 64 suspected ones. Of these, 29 are negative with 32 pending.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-update-no-new-cases-64-suspected-12337246 |title=No new cases of Wuhan virus, 64 suspected cases so far: MOH |date=25 January 2020 |website=CNA |access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref> In addition, MOH imposes a visitor limit of two per patient in hospital.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Teo |first1=Joyce |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/wuhan-virus-only-two-visitors-per-patient-allowed-at-hospitals-children-discouraged |title=Wuhan virus: Only two visitors per patient allowed at hospitals; children discouraged from visiting |date=30 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n**26 January - The fourth case is confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/4th-confirmed-case-of-wuhan-pneumonia-virus-in-singapore-moh-12339912 |title=4th confirmed case of Wuhan virus in Singapore: MOH |date=26 January 2020 |website=CNA |access-date=16\u00a0February 2020}}</ref> Later that day, there are 92 suspect cases, of which 46 are negative.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Chang |first1=Ai-Lien |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-no-new-cases-in-singapore-number-of-confirmed-cases-stands-at-4 |title=Wuhan virus: No new confirmed cases in Singapore, number of suspect cases climbs to 92 |date=26 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=16\u00a0February 2020}}</ref>\n**27 January - \n***[[HardwareZone]] is issued a correction notice over an online post falsely claiming a death in Singapore from the coronavirus. The post is deleted a day before the notice is issued.<ref>{{cite web |title=SPH Magazines complies with Pofma correction order on false HardwareZone post related to the Wuhan virus |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/sph-magazines-complies-with-pofma-correction-order-on-false-hardwarezone-post |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=16 February 2020 |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n***A 14-day leave of absence (LOA) is imposed for students and teachers, as well as those working with vulnerable sectors like pre-schools, healthcare and eldercare returning from mainland China, with students doing home-based learning instead. Temperature screening for all flights will start from 29 January with additional checks on flights from China and passengers from Hubei. In addition, people who travelled to China in the last 14 days will need to fill health and travel declarations and monitor health with temperature checks. MOH will now advise against travel to mainland China. Hostels in [[National University of Singapore]], [[Nanyang Technological University]], and [[Singapore Management University]] will also be designated as quarantine facilities.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chang |first1=Ai-Lien |last2=Khalik |first2=Salma |last3=Kurohi |first3=Rei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-to-impose-14-days-leave-of-absence-for-those-in-schools-healthcare |title=Wuhan virus: Singapore to impose 14 days leave of absence for those in schools, healthcare and eldercare who travelled to China |date=27 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=16 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lai |first1=Linette |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-students-school-staff-returning-from-china-to-take-14-day-mandatory-leave-of |title=Wuhan virus: 2-3 students in every Singapore school likely to be affected by leave of absence |date=27 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=16 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-compulsory-absence-leave-students-teachers-china-12354940 |title=Compulsory leave of absence for students, teachers returning from China: MOE |date=27 January 2020 |website=CNA |access-date=16 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Mahmud |first1=Aqil Haziq |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-hostels-nus-ntu-smu-quarantine-university-students-12357980 |title=NUS, NTU, SMU hostels to be used as quarantine facilities for Wuhan virus |date=27 January 2020 |website=CNA |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Goh |first1=Timothy |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/wuhan-virus-all-inbound-air-travellers-will-undergo-temperature-screening-visual |title=Wuhan virus: All inbound air travellers will undergo temperature screening; visual inspections to be carried out |date=27 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n***The fifth case is confirmed. There are a total of 124 suspect cases, of which 62 are negative.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kurohi |first1=Rei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-confirms-5th-case-patient-from-wuhan-stayed-at-her-familys-home-in |title=Wuhan virus: Singapore confirms 5th case; patient from Wuhan stayed at her family's home in Ceylon Road |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***Taxi companies will waive cab rental fees should any driver be on quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Cara |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/taxi-firms-will-waive-rental-fees-for-cabs-if-drivers-are-quarantined-for-wuhan |title=Coronavirus: Taxi firms will waive rental fees for cabs if drivers are quarantined |date=27 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***A patient was taken from [[Causeway Point]] to a hospital after being suspected of having the virus. The incident was confirmed the following day in a letter.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toh |first1=Ting Wei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/raffles-medical-investigates-photo-of-patients-nric-amid-claims-of-wuhan-virus-case |title=Suspected Wuhan virus case identified at Causeway Point; affected areas disinfected after patient sent to hospital |website=The Straits Times |access-date=23 March 2020 |date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n**28 January - \n***Two more cases are confirmed. A total of 170 suspect cases are tested, with 91 negative. Several new measures are announced as a result, with quarantine for those returning from Hubei and those of a higher risk, and no entry for those from Hubei and visitors who have been there for the last 14 days, starting from noon the next day. All forms of visas for Hubei travellers are suspended immediately.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chang |first1=Ai-Lien |last2=Khalik |first2=Salma |last3=Goh |first3=Timothy |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei |title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref> Those self-employed under quarantine will receive a $100 allowance per day, and home quarantine options are available. Hospital bills will be paid by MOH for all suspected and confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Khalik |first1=Salma |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/100-a-day-for-those-quarantined-severe-penalties-for-people-who-flout-quarantine |title=Wuhan virus: $100 a day for those quarantined; severe penalties for people who flout quarantine orders |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***The [[Ministry of Manpower (Singapore)|Ministry of Manpower]] will reject new applications for workers from Hubei immediately, with existing applications unaffected.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/wuhan-virus-mom-to-reject-all-new-work-pass-applications-for-foreign-workers-from |title=Wuhan virus: MOM to reject all new work pass applications for foreign workers from Hubei |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***[[Facebook]] is issued a correction notice over a post falsely claiming the closure of [[Woodlands MRT station|Woodlands station]] due to the virus.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tham |first1=Yuen-C |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/wuhan-virus-government-debunks-fake-news-linking-closure-of-woodlands-mrt-to-the |title=Govt debunks fake news linking closure of Woodlands MRT station to Wuhan virus |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***NSmen who went to China will be given 14 days leave with all appointments rescheduled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/wuhan-virus-nsmen-who-travelled-to-china-will-have-ict-deferred-ippt-rescheduled |title=Wuhan virus: NSmen who travelled to China will have ICT deferred, IPPT rescheduled |date=28 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n**29 January - \n***Three more cases are confirmed, with 124 suspected cases negative.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-singapore-new-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-12364556 |title=Singapore confirms 3 new cases of Wuhan virus; total of 10 infected |date=29 January 2020 |website=CNA |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***[[Singapore Airlines]] will suspend layovers from the next day for cabin crew and pilots to Beijing and Shanghai. [[Jetstar Asia]] will suspend flights to three cities in China until 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toh |first1=Ting Wei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/no-more-overnight-stay-for-sia-pilots-and-cabin-crew-on-flights-to-beijing-and |title=Wuhan virus: No more overnight stay for SIA pilots and cabin crew on flights to Beijing, Shanghai |date=29 January 2020 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n***The [[National Environment Agency]] released temporary guidelines on disinfecting homes with patients.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goh |first1=Timothy |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/mop-house-twice-with-disinfectant-nea-releases-interim-guide-on-cleani